DEBUG:openai._base_client:Request options: {'method': 'post', 'url': '/embeddings', 'files': None, 'post_parser': <function Embeddings.create.<locals>.parser at 0x12d639280>, 'json_data': {'input': ['The sun was shining and it was beautiful North Carolina weather, yet the climate of\u202c\n\u202dBoy Scout Troop 600 was all but peaceful. Our troop gear trailer was not ready, attendance had\u202c\n\u202dnot been taken, and scouts were just standing around awaiting the next task. The 10+ mile\u202c\n\u202dbackpacking trek that awaited us looked so far away it made the sun-baked horizon look close.\u202c\n\u202dIt was my first campout as the newly assigned Senior Patrol Leader of my 90+ active member\u202c\n\u202dBoy Scout Troop. Early on in my journey as the head youth of my troop, and evident in this early\u202c\n\u202dmemory, I struggled a lot with the concept of “leverage” - I would frequently go to every division\u202c\n\u202dof the troop and monitor what they were struggling with or what they needed, the trailer for\u202c\n\u202dpacking gear, the shed for getting totes, and all the other areas as well.'], 'model': 'text-embedding-3-small', 'encoding_format': 'base64'}}
