DEBUG:openai._base_client:Request options: {'method': 'post', 'url': '/embeddings', 'files': None, 'post_parser': <function Embeddings.create.<locals>.parser at 0x12d65e4c0>, 'json_data': {'input': ['It was after I learned\u202c\n\u202dthis lesson that leadership became fun to me. Leading the troop seemed less like swimming\u202c\n\u202dupstream in a waterfall, and more like leading a large pirate ship with my closest friends. It was\u202c\n\u202dthen that I learned to enjoy leading a group of people towards a common goal and the creative\u202c\n\u202dprocess that comes with it.\u202c\n\u202d3) What is your experience with technology? (\u202c\n\u202d- How have you shared your experiences with technology products and platforms with others?\u202c\n\u202d- What role does technology have in community?\u202c\n\u202d- What developer technology do you find the most interesting and why?\u202c\n\u202d- In what ways are your academic studies integrating / exploring technology?)\u202c\n\u202d(exactly 2000 characters)\u202c\n\u202dEver since my friend introduced me to the Odin Project (full stack course) my first year of\u202c\n\u202dcollege, I have been obsessively learning, building, and coming up with new ideas to solve\u202c\n\u202dproblems and stretch my technical skills. Over the past 3 years, I have learned Node, Angular,\u202c\n\u202dMongoDB, Flask, Nextjs, and Rust, and have participated in 3 hackathons with my friends, 2\u202c\n\u202dresearch projects, and 1 internship not counting countless individual side projects.'], 'model': 'text-embedding-3-small', 'encoding_format': 'base64'}}
