DEBUG:openai._base_client:Request options: {'method': 'post', 'url': '/embeddings', 'files': None, 'post_parser': <function Embeddings.create.<locals>.parser at 0x1178b4dc0>, 'json_data': {'input': ['This is why I want to establish a GDSC chapter at my school—to\u202c\n\u202drecreate the strong sense of community that marching band offers while providing a canvas for\u202c\n\u202dmembers to craft solutions to complex challenges. I am inspired by the idea of guiding the\u202c\n\u202damazing engineering minds in my marching band towards innovation and curiosity, just like I\u202c\n\u202dlove to do in the form of side projects and Computer Science research at my school, and by\u202c\n\u202ddoing this, I hope to build a collaboration between arts and technology and create a home for\u202c\n\u202dmakers. By creating this club and bringing it to my home campus, I would not only create a\u202c\n\u202dspace for makers, but bring along the discipline and perseverance of marching band, allowing\u202c\n\u202dmembers to craft things which are truly extraordinary, and show that the same dedication that\u202c\n\u202dcreates perfect formations on the field can also forge groundbreaking solutions in technology.\u202c\n\u202dAfter my graduation, I want this legacy to live on by encouraging creative and technical\u202c\n\u202dmarching band members to continue taking on leadership roles in the club, and use their\u202c\n\u202dfortitude and discipline to solve the world’s pressing problems, pushing the forefront of\u202c\n\u202dtechnology while carrying the Wolfpack spirit of “Think and Do”.\u202c\n\u202d2) What is your experience in leading a project or a team? (Tell us about your experience as a\u202c\n\u202dteam leader. what was challenging for you, how did you solve problems, what is the best part of\u202c\n\u202dbeing a leader for you?)\u202c\n\u202dKnow about leadership skills + community management + technical skills + community\u202c\n\u202dinitiatives (how you lead a team / how you solved problems I have)\u202c\n\u202d(vvv exactly 2000 characters vvv)\u202c\n\u202d“Delagate delagate delegate” my scoutmaster always told me. It was 7 am and we were behind\u202c\n\u202dschedule.'], 'model': 'text-embedding-3-small', 'encoding_format': 'base64'}}
