INFO:root:{'id': 'chatcmpl-B5tVo3MKWY9lgCZ9ImIaeeWBUuEHq', 'object': 'chat.completion', 'created': 1740744728, 'model': 'gpt-4o-mini-2024-07-18', 'choices': [{'index': 0, 'message': {'role': 'assistant', 'content': None, 'function_call': {'name': 'generate_library_room', 'arguments': '{"lessons":[{"factoids":[{"factoid_text":"The **Boy Scouts** was founded in 1908 by Robert Baden-Powell in England. It aimed to teach young boys skills for outdoor life and citizenship.","question":{"type":"one_word_answer","text":"Who founded the Boy Scouts?","correct_choice":["Robert Baden-Powell"]}},{"factoid_text":"The **Scout Oath** is a promise that every scout makes to do their best, help others, and keep the Scout Law.","question":{"type":"fill_in_the_blank","text":"The Scout Oath includes a promise to do their ___.","correct_choice":["best"],"wrong_choices":["worst","nothing","average"]}},{"factoid_text":"Scouts earn **merit badges** by demonstrating skills in various areas like first aid, cooking, and environmental science.","question":{"type":"multiple_choice","text":"What do scouts earn by demonstrating skills?","correct_choice":["merit badges"],"wrong_choices":["trophies","certificates","medals"]}},{"factoid_text":"The **Scout Law** consists of 12 points that describe how scouts should behave, including being trustworthy and loyal.","question":{"type":"one_word_answer","text":"How many points are in the Scout Law?","correct_choice":["12"]}},{"factoid_text":"Camping is a key activity for scouts, teaching them survival skills and teamwork in the great outdoors.","question":{"type":"fill_in_the_blank","text":"Camping teaches scouts survival skills and ___.","correct_choice":["teamwork"],"wrong_choices":["loneliness","fear","boredom"]}},{"factoid_text":"Scouts participate in community service projects, helping to improve their neighborhoods and support those in need.","question":{"type":"multiple_choice","text":"What type of projects do scouts participate in?","correct_choice":["community service"],"wrong_choices":["sports competitions","art exhibitions","business ventures"]}},{"factoid_text":"The **Eagle Scout** rank is the highest achievement in Boy Scouts, requiring leadership and community service.","question":{"type":"one_word_answer","text":"What is the highest rank in Boy Scouts?","correct_choice":["Eagle Scout"]}},{"factoid_text":"Scouting promotes values like **respect**, **honesty**, and **courage**, which are essential for personal development.","question":{"type":"fill_in_the_blank","text":"Scouting promotes values like respect, honesty, and ___.","correct_choice":["courage"],"wrong_choices":["fear","greed","selfishness"]}},{"factoid_text":"Scouts learn to tie knots, which are essential for various activities like camping, climbing, and sailing.","question":{"type":"multiple_choice","text":"What skill do scouts learn that is essential for camping?","correct_choice":["tying knots"],"wrong_choices":["cooking","drawing","singing"]}}]},{"factoids":[{"factoid_text":"The **Boy Scouts** have a motto: \'Be Prepared,\' which encourages scouts to be ready for any situation.","question":{"type":"one_word_answer","text":"What is the motto of the Boy Scouts?","correct_choice":["Be Prepared"]}},{"factoid_text":"Scouts often go on **campouts**, where they practice skills like cooking over a fire and setting up tents.","question":{"type":"fill_in_the_blank","text":"During campouts, scouts practice cooking over a ___.","correct_choice":["fire"],"wrong_choices":["stove","microwave","grill"]}},{"factoid_text":"The **Boy Scouts of America** was established in 1910 and has since grown to millions of members across the country.","question":{"type":"multiple_choice","text":"In what year was the Boy Scouts of America established?","correct_choice":["1910"],"wrong_choices":["1905","1920","1930"]}},{"factoid_text":"Scouts can earn **ranks** such as Tenderfoot, Second Class, and First Class before reaching Eagle Scout.","question":{"type":"one_word_answer","text":"What is the first rank a scout can earn?","correct_choice":["Tenderfoot"]}},{"factoid_text":"The **Scout Handbook** is a valuable resource that contains information on skills, safety, and scouting history.","question":{"type":"fill_in_the_blank","text":"The Scout Handbook contains information on skills, safety, and ___.","correct_choice":["history"],"wrong_choices":["fashion","sports","music"]}},{"factoid_text":"Scouts learn about **wildlife** and conservation, helping them understand the importance of protecting nature.","question":{"type":"multiple_choice","text":"What do scouts learn about that helps protect nature?","correct_choice":["wildlife"],"wrong_choices":["cars","buildings","technology"]}},{"factoid_text":"The **World Scout Movement** connects scouts from different countries, promoting friendship and understanding.","question":{"type":"one_word_answer","text":"What connects scouts from different countries?","correct_choice":["World Scout Movement"]}},{"factoid_text":"Scouts often participate in **jamborees**, which are large gatherings of scouts from around the world.","question":{"type":"fill_in_the_blank","text":"Large gatherings of scouts are called ___.","correct_choice":["jamborees"],"wrong_choices":["meetings","parties","conferences"]}},{"factoid_text":"Scouting encourages **leadership** skills, helping scouts become responsible and active members of their communities.","question":{"type":"multiple_choice","text":"What type of skills does scouting encourage?","correct_choice":["leadership"],"wrong_choices":["singing","drawing","cooking"]}}]},{"factoids":[{"factoid_text":"The **Boy Scouts** have a strong emphasis on **outdoor** activities, which help build confidence and resilience.","question":{"type":"one_word_answer","text":"What type of activities do Boy Scouts emphasize?","correct_choice":["outdoor"]}},{"factoid_text":"Scouts learn to **navigate** using maps and compasses, which is essential for hiking and camping.","question":{"type":"fill_in_the_blank","text":"Scouts learn to navigate using maps and ___.","correct_choice":["compasses"],"wrong_choices":["GPS","smartphones","radios"]}},{"factoid_text":"The **Cub Scouts** is a program for younger boys, focusing on fun and learning through games and activities.","question":{"type":"multiple_choice","text":"What is the program for younger boys called?","correct_choice":["Cub Scouts"],"wrong_choices":["Boy Scouts","Eagle Scouts","Webelos"]}},{"factoid_text":"Scouts are encouraged to set **goals** and work towards achieving them, fostering a sense of accomplishment.","question":{"type":"one_word_answer","text":"What are scouts encouraged to set and achieve?","correct_choice":["goals"]}},{"factoid_text":"The **Scout Spirit** is about having a positive attitude and helping others, embodying the values of scouting.","question":{"type":"fill_in_the_blank","text":"The Scout Spirit embodies a positive attitude and ___.","correct_choice":["helping others"],"wrong_choices":["being selfish","ignoring others","complaining"]}},{"factoid_text":"Scouts often learn **first aid**, which is crucial for handling emergencies during outdoor activities.","question":{"type":"multiple_choice","text":"What skill is crucial for handling emergencies?","correct_choice":["first aid"],"wrong_choices":["cooking","singing","drawing"]}},{"factoid_text":"Scouting promotes **diversity**, welcoming boys from all backgrounds and cultures to join and learn together.","question":{"type":"one_word_answer","text":"What does scouting promote among its members?","correct_choice":["diversity"]}},{"factoid_text":"Scouts participate in **fundraising** activities to support their troops and community projects.","question":{"type":"fill_in_the_blank","text":"Scouts participate in fundraising activities to support their ___.","correct_choice":["troops"],"wrong_choices":["families","friends","schools"]}},{"factoid_text":"The **Scout motto** and **law** are essential parts of a scout\'s identity, guiding their actions and decisions.","question":{"type":"multiple_choice","text":"What are essential parts of a scout\'s identity?","correct_choice":["motto and law"],"wrong_choices":["uniform and badge","campfire and songs","friends and family"]}}]}]}'}, 'refusal': None}, 'logprobs': None, 'finish_reason': 'stop'}], 'usage': {'prompt_tokens': 1187, 'completion_tokens': 1730, 'total_tokens': 2917, 'prompt_tokens_details': {'cached_tokens': 0, 'audio_tokens': 0}, 'completion_tokens_details': {'reasoning_tokens': 0, 'audio_tokens': 0, 'accepted_prediction_tokens': 0, 'rejected_prediction_tokens': 0}}, 'service_tier': 'default', 'system_fingerprint': 'fp_06737a9306'}
