INFO:root:{'id': 'chatcmpl-B5uEn5MrCvC9Q1kZLqiaJMItglo1E', 'object': 'chat.completion', 'created': 1740747517, 'model': 'gpt-4o-mini-2024-07-18', 'choices': [{'index': 0, 'message': {'role': 'assistant', 'content': None, 'function_call': {'name': 'generate_library_room', 'arguments': '{"lessons":[{"factoids":[{"factoid_text":"A **marching band** is a group of musicians who perform while marching, often in parades or at sports events. They combine music with visual performance, creating a dynamic spectacle.","question":{"type":"one_word_answer","text":"What is a group of musicians who perform while marching called?","correct_choice":["marching band"]}},{"factoid_text":"Marching bands typically consist of **brass**, **woodwind**, and **percussion** instruments. Each section plays a unique role in creating the overall sound.","question":{"type":"multiple_choice","text":"What types of instruments are commonly found in a marching band?","correct_choice":["brass, woodwind, percussion"],"wrong_choices":["strings, piano, drums","guitar, flute, saxophone","only brass instruments"]}},{"factoid_text":"The **drum major** is the leader of a marching band, responsible for directing the band during performances and ensuring everyone stays in sync.","question":{"type":"fill_in_the_blank","text":"The leader of a marching band is called the ___.","correct_choice":["drum major"],"wrong_choices":["band captain","conductor","soloist"]}},{"factoid_text":"Marching bands often perform intricate **choreography** while playing music, which adds a visual element to their performances.","question":{"type":"multiple_choice","text":"What do marching bands add to their performances besides music?","correct_choice":["choreography"],"wrong_choices":["solo performances","silent movements","only marching"]}},{"factoid_text":"**Uniforms** are an essential part of a marching band’s identity. They often feature bright colors and unique designs to stand out during performances.","question":{"type":"one_w