INFO:root:{'id': 'chatcmpl-B5uEmf45gKwhr4QB2nMUvhhq0uhgT', 'object': 'chat.completion', 'created': 1740747516, 'model': 'gpt-4o-mini-2024-07-18', 'choices': [{'index': 0, 'message': {'role': 'assistant', 'content': None, 'function_call': {'name': 'generate_library_room', 'arguments': '{"lessons":[{"factoids":[{"factoid_text":"**Technology** is the application of scientific knowledge for practical purposes. It can be found in everyday items like smartphones, computers, and even kitchen appliances!","question":{"type":"one_word_answer","text":"What is the application of scientific knowledge for practical purposes?","correct_choice":["technology"]}},{"factoid_text":"The **internet** is a vast network that connects millions of computers worldwide, allowing for the sharing of information and communication. It\'s like a giant web that links us all!","question":{"type":"fill_in_the_blank","text":"The vast network that connects millions of computers worldwide is called the ___.","correct_choice":["internet"],"wrong_choices":["intranet","extranet","web"]}},{"factoid_text":"**Artificial Intelligence (AI)** refers to machines that can perform tasks that typically require human intelligence, such as understanding language and recognizing patterns. Think of it as a brain for computers!","question":{"type":"multiple_choice","text":"What does AI stand for?","correct_choice":["Artificial Intelligence"],"wrong_choices":["Automated Information","Advanced Integration","Artificial Interaction"]}},{"factoid_text":"**Robotics** is a branch of technology that deals with the design, construction, and operation of robots. These machines can perform tasks ranging from assembly line work to exploring Mars!","question":{"type":"one_word_answer","text":"What branch of technology deals with robots?","correct_choice":["robotics"]}},{"factoid_text":"The **cloud** refers to storing and accessing data and programs over the internet instead of on your computer\'s hard drive. It\'s like having a virtual storage room!","question":{"type":"fill_in_the_blank","text":"Storing and accessing data over the internet is known as ___.","correct_choice":["cloud"],"wrong_choices":["local storage","data center","hard drive"]}},{"factoid_text":"**Virtual Reality (VR)** immerses users in a computer-generated environment, allowing them to interact with 3D worlds. It\'s like stepping into a video game!","question":{"type":"multiple_choice","text":"What technology immerses users in a computer-generated environment?","correct_choice":["Virtual Reality"],"wrong_choices":["Augmented Reality","Mixed Reality","Digital Reality"]}},{"factoid_text":"**Blockchain** is a decentralized digital ledger that records transactions across many computers. This technology is the backbone of cryptocurrencies like Bitcoin!","question":{"type":"one_word_answer","text":"What technology is the backbone of cryptocurrencies?","correct_choice":["blockchain"]}},{"factoid_text":"**Wearable technology** includes devices like smartwatches and fitness trackers that monitor health and activity. They are like personal assistants on your wrist!","question":{"type":"fill_in_the_blank","text":"Devices like smartwatches that monitor health are called ___.","correct_choice":["wearable technology"],"wrong_choices":["mobile apps","smart devices","fitness gadgets"]}},{"factoid_text":"**5G technology** is the fifth generation of mobile networks, offering faster speeds and more reliable connections. It\'s like upgrading from a bicycle to a sports car!","question":{"type":"multiple_choice","text":"What is the fifth generation of mobile networks called?","correct_choice":["5G technology"],"wrong_choices":["4G technology","3G technology","LTE technology"]}}]},{"factoids":[{"factoid_text":"**Cybersecurity** is the practice of protecting systems, networks, and programs from digital attacks. It\'s like having a security guard for your online data!","question":{"type":"one_word_answer","text":"What is the practice of protecting systems from digital attacks?","correct_choice":["cybersecurity"]}},{"factoid_text":"**Big Data** refers to extremely large data sets that can be analyzed to reveal patterns, trends, and associations. It\'s like finding a needle in a haystack, but the needle is information!","question":{"type":"fill_in_the_blank","text":"Extremely large data sets that reveal patterns are known as ___.","correct_choice":["big data"],"wrong_choices":["small data","data mining","data analytics"]}},{"factoid_text":"**E-commerce** is the buying and selling of goods and services over the internet. It\'s like having a store that never closes!","question":{"type":"multiple_choice","text":"What is the buying and selling of goods over the internet called?","correct_choice":["E-commerce"],"wrong_choices":["E-business","Online shopping","Digital marketing"]}},{"factoid_text":"**Augmented Reality (AR)** overlays digital information onto the real world, enhancing our perception of reality. It\'s like adding a filter to your view!","question":{"type":"one_word_answer","text":"What technology overlays digital information onto the real world?","correct_choice":["augmented reality"]}},{"factoid_text":"**Smart homes** are residences equipped with devices that can be controlled remotely via the internet. Imagine controlling your lights and thermostat from your phone!","question":{"type":"fill_in_the_blank","text":"Residences equipped with internet-controlled devices are called ___.","correct_choice":["smart homes"],"wrong_choices":["traditional homes","connected homes","automated homes"]}},{"factoid_text":"**3D printing** allows for the creation of three-dimensional objects from a digital file. It\'s like a magic printer that can make toys, tools, and even food!","question":{"type":"multiple_choice","text":"What technology creates three-dimensional objects from digital files?","correct_choice":["3D printing"],"wrong_choices":["2D printing","Laser cutting","CNC machining"]}},{"factoid_text":"**Social media** platforms allow users to create and share content or participate in social networking. It\'s like a digital gathering place for friends!","question":{"type":"one_word_answer","text":"What platforms allow users to share content and network socially?","correct_choice":["social media"]}},{"factoid_text":"**Digital marketing** uses online platforms to promote products and services. It\'s like advertising, but in the virtual world!","question":{"type":"fill_in_the_blank","text":"Promoting products using online platforms is known as ___.","correct_choice":["digital marketing"],"wrong_choices":["traditional marketing","offline marketing","direct marketing"]}},{"factoid_text":"**Telecommuting** allows employees to work from home or remote locations using technology. It\'s like bringing the office to your living room!","question":{"type":"multiple_choice","text":"What allows employees to work from home using technology?","correct_choice":["Telecommuting"],"wrong_choices":["Commuting","Remote working","Office working"]}}]},{"factoids":[{"factoid_text":"**Tech startups** are new companies focused on developing innovative technologies. They are like the fresh fish in the ocean of business!","question":{"type":"one_word_answer","text":"What are new companies focused on innovative technologies called?","correct_choice":["tech startups"]}},{"factoid_text":"**Open-source software** is software with source code that anyone can inspect, modify, and enhance. It\'s like a recipe that everyone can tweak!","question":{"type":"fill_in_the_blank","text":"Software that anyone can modify is known as ___.","correct_choice":["open-source software"],"wrong_choices":["proprietary software","commercial software","closed-source software"]}},{"factoid_text":"**Fintech** refers to technology that improves and automates the delivery of financial services. It\'s like having a bank in your pocket!","question":{"type":"multiple_choice","text":"What technology improves financial services?","correct_choice":["Fintech"],"wrong_choices":["Healthtech","Edtech","Agtech"]}},{"factoid_text":"**Data privacy** is the right of individuals to control their personal information. It\'s like having a lock on your diary!","question":{"type":"one_word_answer","text":"What is the right to control personal information called?","correct_choice":["data privacy"]}},{"factoid_text":"**Tech literacy** is the ability to use technology effectively. It\'s like learning to ride a bike; once you know how, you can go anywhere!","question":{"type":"fill_in_the_blank","text":"The ability to use technology effectively is known as ___.","correct_choice":["tech literacy"],"wrong_choices":["digital literacy","computer skills","IT knowledge"]}},{"factoid_text":"**Quantum computing** uses quantum bits (qubits) to perform calculations at incredible speeds. It\'s like having a super-fast calculator that can solve complex problems!","question":{"type":"multiple_choice","text":"What type of computing uses quantum bits?","correct_choice":["Quantum computing"],"wrong_choices":["Classical computing","Supercomputing","Parallel computing"]}},{"factoid_text":"**Biotechnology** combines biology and technology to develop products and processes. It\'s like using nature\'s tools to create new solutions!","question":{"type":"one_word_answer","text":"What combines biology and technology to develop new products?","correct_choice":["biotechnology"]}},{"factoid_text":"**Digital transformation** is the integration of digital technology into all areas of a business. It\'s like turning a traditional store into an online marketplace!","question":{"type":"fill_in_the_blank","text":"Integrating digital technology into all areas of a business is called ___.","correct_choice":["digital transformation"],"wrong_choices":["business innovation","digital marketing","e-commerce"]}},{"factoid_text":"**Tech ethics** examines the moral implications of technology use. It\'s like asking, \\"Is this the right thing to do?\\" in the tech world!","question":{"type":"multiple_choice","text":"What examines the moral implications of technology?","correct_choice":["Tech ethics"],"wrong_choices":["Tech policy","Tech law","Tech philosophy"]}}]}]}'}, 'refusal': None}, 'logprobs': None, 'finish_reason': 'stop'}], 'usage': {'prompt_tokens': 1184, 'completion_tokens': 2000, 'total_tokens': 3184, 'prompt_tokens_details': {'cached_tokens': 0, 'audio_tokens': 0}, 'completion_tokens_details': {'reasoning_tokens': 0, 'audio_tokens': 0, 'accepted_prediction_tokens': 0, 'rejected_prediction_tokens': 0}}, 'service_tier': 'default', 'system_fingerprint': 'fp_06737a9306'}
